<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a7e1b87-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s7806"><num value="7806">§ 7806.</num><heading> Limitation</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this chapter shall be construed to prohibit an individual from seeking any remedies available under existing Federal or State law or equity.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7a7e1b88-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/108/304/s7">Pub. L. 108–304, § 7</ref>, <date date="2004-09-24">Sept. 24, 2004</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/118/1128">118 Stat. 1128</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
